Class CoverageRanker

java.lang.Object
  qqa.ml.Ranker
      qqa.ml.CoverageRanker

public class CoverageRanker
extends Ranker

Contains the tools to rank sentences according to their relevance to a query. Used to generate a question-biased summary of the answers to a specific question

Author:
Mattia Tomasoni

                               javax.xml.parsers.ParserConfigurationException,
                               org.xml.sax.SAXException
Temporarily populates the similarAnswers Vector. Uses the Yahoo! API to retrieve a set of similar answers, saves them to an xml file then parses its content and adds it (in the form of a set of words) in the similarAnswers Vector

computeTermFrequency

private void computeTermFrequency(java.lang.String answer_content)
Temporarily populates the termFrequency table. for each term in the current answer, adds an entry in the termFrequency table with its corresponding number of occurrences.

Parameters:
answer_content -

computeCoverageScore

private java.lang.Double computeCoverageScore(java.lang.String answer_content)
Computes the coverage score for the current answer as explained in Essential Pages. For each term computes the term relevance and from it the term importance. All term importance scores multiplied by their term frequencies are summed. The result is returned as the coverage.

Parameters:
answer_content -
